data-test="review-card--text">My Yorkie loves this bed. She likes the high walls to lay against and the low entry way for her cute little shortstack legs. Easy for her to get in and out of. It washes well when washed gently alone and dried on medium heat. Only complaint regarding this item is that I put this bed in my shopping cart last night wanting to buy her a second one, for the upstairs in my house, but now it‚Äôs $5 more today. A 25% price increase to be exact. That‚Äôs a bit much for a price hike over night. And no, it wasn‚Äôt on sale yesterday. It‚Äôs been the same price for a few months now. In this economy where people‚Äôs incomes aren‚Äôt increasing, but they still keep price gouging us, it feels a bit high. Especially when we can get beds like this for half the price at discount stores. I won‚Äôt say the names, but they‚Äôre popular stores; they rhyme with Smross and Smarshalls. Lol Therefore I will pass on buying a second one and spend my money elsewhere. Unless they fix the price lower. Maybe someone made a mistake? I know in California it‚Äôs illegal to increase prices more than 10%, so maybe it was an oversight by someone? purchaser</span></span></div><div class="h-margin-t-default h-text-md" data-test="review-card--text">So my cat hates it, but it's not the bed's fault. This review is about what I like about it and the construction. I bought it in preparation for adopting my cat, not knowing that he actually hates warm, soft, squishy things like cat beds. *sigh* Such is life, such are cats. That being said, this is the first cat bed I've seen that can truly be washed and dried. Before my cat arrived and turned his nose up at it, I did just that, and it held up beautifully. I was so impressed and honestly very sad he had no interest in it because it's so well constructed! Anyway, if you have a cat that does like soft, squishy, warm stuff, and you also like things that are easy to clean, I highly recommend this bed. You will love it.</div></div><div class="styles__FixedWidthDiv-sc-4u2mi2-5 klYbun secondary-rating-with-feedback h-display-flex h-flex-direction-col"><div class="styles__GrowDiv-sc-4u2mi2-2 function deepFreeze(object) {
  var propNames = Object.getOwnPropertyNames(object);

  // Freeze properties before freezing self
  for (var name of propNames) {
    var value = object[name];
    if (value && typeof value === "object") {
      deepFreeze(value);
    }
  }
  return Object.freeze(object);
}
